section.section:
The department shall cause the veterans' personal loan program trust fund to lend a qualified veteran or deceased veteran's unremarried spouse not more than ten thousand dollars ($10,000), or a lesser amount established by an administrative regulation promulgated by the department, for:
The purchase of a home, business, or business property;
The education of the loan applicant or the loan applicant's spouse;
The payment of family medical or funeral expenses; or
The consolidation of debt.

The veterans' personal loan program trust fund may:
Compromise indebtedness;
Sue and be sued;
Post bonds;
Write off indebtedness that it considers uncollectible;
Exercise the rights of an owner and mortgagee if a loan provided under this section is secured by a real estate mortgage;
Charge to a loan applicant loan expenses incurred under this section; and
Receive state appropriations, gifts, grants, federal funds, and any other funds both public and private.
Funds received, which are not necessary for the operation of the veterans' personal loan program trust fund, shall remain with the department to finance other department operations.
